Rating: 0
I changed the recipe and it came out AMAZING. I don't know how the original one was, but I had my doubts. Also this version is really enough for 8-6 people. 2 small or 1.5 large white onions diced 3 cloves of garlic minced one cayenne pepper (small) minced (optional can substitute for a few dashes of tabasco or just dried cayenne pepper (2 tsp's) 2-3 tab's of oil 2 tabs of butter 2.5 tabs of brown sugar 2 tsp of cumin 1 tsp chili powder 1/4 tsp nutmeg 6 cups of chicken stock (and or 6 cups of water with the appropriate amt of veg or chicken bouillon cubes) 1 cup of milk or cream (i used skim) about 30 oz (1 large can) of unsweetened pumpkin puree- you can use a can and a half though corn (i used 2 cans) black beans (1 can) about 1 cup to 3/4 of a cup of cilantro chopped roughly throw first paragraph of ingredients in a soup pot at low heat. allow to mingle with minimum stirring for about 1/2 hr so that the onions slightly caramelize. add the spices and incorporate. add the broth and milk. allow to come to a simmer. when hot whisk in the pumpkin. I have a soup blender, so I blended the ingredients at this point. you can use a regular blender and just run it through in batches. i'm not sure but the soup may be fine without this step. once blended you can add whatever southwestern ingredients you like. i listed just corn, black beans, and cilantro but i'm sure there are others i did not think about. and it is ready to serve.

