Because I HATE pumpkin I used sweet potatoes for this dish. And what a dish it was! Flavor beyond compare, hearty, creamy... what more could a dish ask for? I did make a few changes other than the sweet potatoes. I did not have any whipping cream, but I did have a small can of evaporated milk. Also, I peeled and sliced my potatoes and brought them to a vigorous boil in the chicken broth, mashing them frequently. I then threw in my spices (used cayenne instead of chili powder - I was out), excluding coriandor and nutmeg, though we added two cloves of garlic, and continued to let it boil like crazy. The more it boiled, the thicker it got. We served it with the cheese and cilantro. The cheese as a great mellow flavor in contrast with the spice of the soup. My husband couldn't stop sampling it while it was cooking. He raved about the soup all night! I was very impressed with this simple, yet truly delicious, dish.

Rating: 4
DELICIOUS - QUICK - EASY What more can you ask for in a recipe. I made this for lunch with a friend. It was like something from a fancy restaraunt. To make it thicker and creamier, I only used 1 1/2 cups of chicken broth. I also used 1/2 & 1/2 instead of the whip cream. I wish I could give this more then 4 forks. The flavors blended so nicely. I can't wait to make it again.

