Rating: 4
I have made pumpkin soup several different ways, usually involving onions and potatoes and lots of time and work. This soup was BETTER and took far less time. I left out the sharp cheddar cheese COMPLETELY since I was having grilled cheese sandwiches with the soup, and added another cup of broth, used 1.5 cups of evaporated milk instead of whipping cream, and about 18 ounces of roasted and pureed pumpkin with very little moisture. I also used a little more spice and cut the brown sugar by more than half. This soup was excellent, and I will definitely make it again. As a fan of the bland potato-pumpkin variety, where you add tons of nutmeg to give it any flavor, I was surprised that I liked this as much as I did. (I shouldn't tell you this, but the pumpkin had been in the freezer for about 14 months, and the spices completely covered any freezer-taste that might have otherwise spoiled a dish.)

